			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polyvinylchloride, commonly known as PVC, in its bulk polymerised form. This describes the substance in its processed state as a polymer that has been polymerised in bulk without the use of solvents. It includes details about the polymerization process, the quality and standards it meets, potential applications, production method, and the name of the starting monomer. The product flow may indicate whether it is being supplied as a production or consumption mix and the point in the supply chain it is available, such as to consumers or at the plant.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">聚氯乙烯，通常称为PVC，是以散装聚合形式存在的。这描述了该物质作为一种已经以散装方式进行聚合而无需使用溶剂的聚合物的加工状态。它包括关于聚合过程、它满足的质量和标准、潜在应用、生产方法以及起始单体的名称的详细信息。产品流可能表明它是作为生产或消费混合物提供的，以及在供应链中的可用点，例如对消费者或在工厂。</common:generalComment>
